Props drilling -read docs

Data flow in react is one way from parent components to child components.
In a large application this can become a problem or a tedious thing to maintain.
One way is to keep passing the data as props from the topmost parent down to the child which needs the data, this is called props drilling.

React context - like a global space and anyone can access data from it
like a central store of data,
ex - data of a logged in user, because this can be used in many places in a app

